eagle-adsl (1.0.4-4) unstable; urgency=low

  * Fixed description of eagle-adsl-data (which no longer contains the
    firmware). 
  * Switched to Architecture: any (closes: #200806).
  * eagle-adsl-tools now no longer depends on eagle-adsl-modules but only
    recommends it.  This should allow people to use their own
    hand-compiled kernels.  Documented the change in README.Debian.
  * Updated Debconf templates for better phrasing of boolean questions.
    Patch from Christian Perrier <bubulle@debian.org> applied almost
    as-is, many thanks to him (closes: #201284).
  * Bumped Standards-Version: to 3.6, no changes necessary.

